        "narration": [
          {
            "id": "narr_01",
            "file_path": "audios/narr-01.mp3",
            "start_time": 0.0,
            "volume": 1.0,
            "subtitle": {
              "text": "The story of artificial intelligence begins in 1950, when Alan Turing asked a groundbreaking question."
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "narr_02",
            "file_path": "audios/narr-02.mp3",
            "start_time": 8.552,
            "volume": 1.0,
            "subtitle": {
              "text": "Can machines think? Turing proposed the Imitation Game, now known as the Turing Test."
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "narr_03",
            "file_path": "audios/narr-03.mp3",
            "start_time": 16.744,
            "volume": 1.0,
            "subtitle": {
              "text": "In the 1960s and 70s, researchers built expert systems, programs that mimicked human decision-making."
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "narr_04",
            "file_path": "audios/narr-04.mp3",
            "start_time": 25.824,
            "volume": 1.0,
            "subtitle": {
              "text": "But early AI was limited by hardware and data. Progress stalled, leading to the first AI Winter."
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "narr_05",
            "file_path": "audios/narr-05.mp3",
            "start_time": 34.832,
            "volume": 1.0,
            "subtitle": {
              "text": "In 1997, IBM's Deep Blue defeated world chess champion Garry Kasparov, marking a historic comeback."
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "narr_06",
            "file_path": "audios/narr-06.mp3",
            "start_time": 45.088,
            "volume": 1.0,
            "subtitle": {
              "text": "The 2000s brought a revolution in machine learning, powered by bigger data and faster computers."
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "narr_07",
            "file_path": "audios/narr-07.mp3",
            "start_time": 53.352,
            "volume": 1.0,
            "subtitle": {
              "text": "In 2012, deep learning made a breakthrough when AlexNet crushed the image recognition competition."
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "narr_08",
            "file_path": "audios/narr-08.mp3",
            "start_time": 61.712,
            "volume": 1.0,
            "subtitle": {
              "text": "Then in 2017, researchers at Google introduced the Transformer architecture, changing everything."
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "narr_09",
            "file_path": "audios/narr-09.mp3",
            "start_time": 70.696,
            "volume": 1.0,
            "subtitle": {
              "text": "Transformers enabled GPT models to generate human-like text, images, and even code."
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "narr_10",
            "file_path": "audios/narr-10.mp3",
            "start_time": 78.552,
            "volume": 1.0,
            "subtitle": {
              "text": "ChatGPT, launched in 2022, brought AI into everyday life for millions of people."
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "narr_11",
            "file_path": "audios/narr-11.mp3",
            "start_time": 87.008,
            "volume": 1.0,
            "subtitle": {
              "text": "Today, AI is everywhere, from self-driving cars to medical diagnosis and creative arts."
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "narr_12",
            "file_path": "audios/narr-12.mp3",
            "start_time": 95.776,
            "volume": 1.0,
            "subtitle": {
              "text": "The journey of AI has only just begun. The future is being written, one algorithm at a time."
            }
          }
        ],
